---
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Cookie Policy | Soraia";
const description =
  "Information on the use of cookies and similar technologies on the soraia.io website, pursuant to the Italian Data Protection Authority's Provision of 10 June 2021 and EU Regulation 2016/679.";

const lastUpdate = "1 October 2026";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} lang="en">
  <article class="legal-page">
    <header class="legal-hero">
      <div class="container-soraia">
        <nav class="legal-breadcrumb">
          <a href="/en/">Home</a> <span>›</span> <span>Cookie Policy</span>
        </nav>
        <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal document</p>
        <h1 class="legal-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdate}</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="legal-body">
      <div class="container-soraia max-w-3xl">
        <p class="legal-intro">
          This Cookie Policy describes the types of cookies and similar technologies used on the <strong>soraia.io</strong> website, the purposes for which they are used, and how users can manage them. It is drafted pursuant to the Provision of the Italian Data Protection Authority (Garante per la Protezione dei Dati Personali) of 10 June 2021 and EU Regulation 2016/679 (GDPR).
        </p>

        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-soft); font-size: 14px;"><em>This English translation is provided for convenience. The Italian version prevails in case of discrepancy.</em></p>

        <h2>1. What are cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that websites send to a user's device (computer, tablet, smartphone) during browsing, which are stored and retransmitted to the website on subsequent visits. Similar technologies (local storage, pixels, fingerprinting) may serve analogous functions and are treated as equivalent to cookies for the purposes of this policy.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Soraia's approach</h2>
        <p>
          Soraia adopts a <strong>privacy-first</strong> approach: the soraia.io website is designed to operate with the fewest possible cookies and without third-party advertising trackers. We do not use behavioural profiling, retargeting, or targeted advertising tools.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Types of cookies used</h2>

        <h3>3.1. Essential technical cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These are cookies strictly necessary for the operation of the website and the delivery of services requested by the user. They do not require prior consent (Art. 122 Italian Privacy Code). They include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Security and attack-mitigation cookies (e.g. CDN anti-bot cookies).</li>
          <li>Load-balancing and technical session cookies.</li>
          <li>Local storage of user preferences (e.g. selected language).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2. Third-party cookies</h3>
        <p>
          The website integrates a single third-party resource that sets essential technical cookies for its own operation:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare</strong>: used as a Content Delivery Network and for security/anti-bot purposes. It sets consent-exempt technical cookies to protect the website. More information: <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The website's <strong>typefaces</strong> are hosted directly on our own domain (self-hosted): no requests are made to third-party services (e.g. Google Fonts) to load fonts.
        </p>

        <h3>3.3. Analytics cookies</h3>
        <p>
          At this time, the website does not use third-party analytics tools (e.g. Google Analytics, Hotjar, Meta Pixel) that require prior consent. Any internal traffic measurement tools used in the future will be configured to be assimilable to technical cookies (anonymised IP, no cross-site tracking, no sharing with third parties for marketing purposes).
        </p>

        <h3>3.4. Profiling and marketing cookies</h3>
        <p>
          Soraia <strong>does not use profiling, retargeting, advertising, or social media tracking cookies</strong> on its website. No cookies intended to build user profiles for direct marketing purposes, by Soraia or third parties, are set.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Cookie duration</h2>
        <p>The technical cookies used have varying durations:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Session cookies</strong>: automatically deleted when the browser is closed.</li>
          <li><strong>Persistent cookies</strong>: retained for a predetermined period, typically between 24 hours and 12 months depending on the technical purpose.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. User cookie management</h2>
        <p>
          Users may at any time manage, block, or delete cookies through their browser settings. Disabling essential technical cookies may impair the proper functioning of the website.
        </p>
        <p>Instructions for the main browsers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Chrome</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/it/kb/Attivare%20e%20disattivare%20i%20cookie" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/it-it/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/it-it/microsoft-edge/eliminare-i-cookie-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Data transfers and non-EU providers</h2>
        <p>
          Some of the technology providers mentioned (e.g. Google, Cloudflare) are based in the United States or operate with global infrastructure. Data transfers take place in compliance with the safeguards provided for under the GDPR, in particular through Standard Contractual Clauses adopted by the European Commission and, where applicable, on the basis of adequacy decisions (e.g. EU-US Data Privacy Framework).
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to the Cookie Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This Cookie Policy may be updated in response to technical, organisational, or regulatory changes. The current version is always available on this page, together with the date of the last update.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For any enquiry regarding this Cookie Policy or the use of cookies on the website:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Soraia S.r.l.</strong><br/>
          Via Losana 13, 13900 Biella (BI)<br/>
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@soraia.io">info@soraia.io</a>
        </p>

        <p style="margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line, #e4e4e7); font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--color-ink-soft, #6b7280);">
          Regulatory references: EU Regulation 2016/679 (GDPR), Legislative Decree 196/2003 as amended by Legislative Decree 101/2018 (Italian Privacy Code), Provision of the Italian Data Protection Authority of 10 June 2021 "Guidelines on cookies and other tracking tools".
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style is:global>
    .legal-page { background: #fff; }
    .legal-hero {
      padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
      background: var(--color-ink-50, #FAFAF8);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line, #e4e4e7);
    }
    .legal-breadcrumb {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--color-ink-soft, #6b7280);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .legal-breadcrumb a {
      color: var(--color-ink-soft, #6b7280);
      transition: opacity 200ms;
    }
    .legal-breadcrumb a:hover { opacity: 0.7; }
    .legal-eyebrow {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--color-ink-soft, #6b7280);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .legal-title {
      font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 0.5rem, 3.5rem);
      line-height: 1.05;
      letter-spacing: -0.025em;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-ink, #0a0a0a);
      text-wrap: balance;
    }
    .legal-meta {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 13.5px;
      color: var(--color-ink-soft, #6b7280);
    }
    .legal-body {
      padding: 4rem 0 6rem;
      font-size: 15.5px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-ink, #0a0a0a);
    }
    .legal-body .legal-intro {
      font-size: 17px;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--color-ink-muted, #4b5563);
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line, #e4e4e7);
      text-wrap: pretty;
    }
    .legal-body h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
      letter-spacing: -0.018em;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-ink, #0a0a0a);
      margin-top: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }
    .legal-body h3 {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
      letter-spacing: -0.012em;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-ink, #0a0a0a);
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
    }
    .legal-body p {
      margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--color-ink, #0a0a0a);
      text-wrap: pretty;
    }
    .legal-body strong { font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink, #0a0a0a); }
    .legal-body ul, .legal-body ol {
      padding-left: 1.4rem;
      margin: 1.1rem 0 1.4rem;
    }
    .legal-body ul { list-style: disc; }
    .legal-body ol { list-style: decimal; }
    .legal-body li { margin: 0.55rem 0; line-height: 1.65; text-wrap: pretty; }
    .legal-body li::marker { color: var(--color-ink-soft, #6b7280); }
    .legal-body a {
      color: var(--color-brand, #4A1E5C);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
      transition: opacity 200ms;
    }
    .legal-body a:hover { opacity: 0.7; }
  </style>
</Layout>
